{"title":"Chris McNally Boxers? Ornot…","link":"https://theradavist.com/chris-mcnally-boxers-ornot/","date":1743696553000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_hero.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_hero.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_hero.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_hero.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em>San Francisco artist <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/chris-mcnally/\" target=\"_blank\">Chris McNally</a> has made himself known working with brands like Paul Component Engineering, White Industries, Hunter Cycles, Ibis Cycles, Blackburn, our own <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/camera-corner-documentary-wende-cragg/\" target=\"_blank\">Camera Corner film</a>, and clothing brand Ornot. But today he made brief history with the launch of his <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;merchant_id=34a711d0-83d2-4a96-8e01-9f5ea4abd1fc&amp;website_id=6ec3743b-a948-4c16-9d12-4b79ac107f25&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ornotbike.com%2Fproducts%2Fmens-ultralight-boxer-briefs-mcnally\" target=\"_blank\">Ornot boxers</a>…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_ornot-03.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_ornot-03.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_ornot-03.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_ornot-03.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_ornot-01.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_ornot-01.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_ornot-01.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_ornot-01.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_ornot-02.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_ornot-02.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_ornot-02.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/Chris_McNally_Boxers_ornot-02.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Ten years of Chris McNally’s sketchbook, now on ultralight boxers. Every pair’s a little different—taco stops, SF streets, airport doodles, and occasional misspellings. Cut and sewn in California—light and made for hot days, sketchy routes, or long layovers. Thoughtfully constructed with Oeko-Tex-approved recycled fabric, the open-box mesh fabric masters moisture-wicking and breathability. The flyless pouch adds a simple convenience, while the odor-resistant property keeps things fresh.</p>\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Flatlock seams for comfort</li>\n<li>Full gusset</li>\n<li>Soft waistband</li>\n<li>OEKO-TEX® Standard 100 recycled fabric – 85% Polyester 15% Lycra, 115gsm</li>\n<li>Constructed with bluesign®-approved materials</li>\n<li>Sewn by hand in Oakland, California</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Pick up a pair at <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/chris-mcnally/\" target=\"_blank\">Ornot</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/chris-mcnally-boxers-ornot/\">Chris McNally Boxers? Ornot…</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"51f37d7fccf54166568ca3002b641ad23404146faae41bbd5137619a118c636a","category":"Cycling"}